channel.title: No-Ip DUC problem
channel.description:
It opens and I enter my email and password that i use on the No-Ip.com website. It gives me an error and says " An error has occured, Please verify username and password. "
This is very frustrating, would appreciate help.

item.title: No-Ip DUC problem
item.dc:creator: @PvM_Micro PvM Micro
item.description:
@PvM_Micro wrote:

** FOR ANYONE WITH A SIMILAR PROBLEM, THIS IS HOW I FIXED IT.

I was thinking that if this DUC is anything like an RSPS server, it would need to be in the correct folder to operate correctly. When I first downloaded it i moved the DUC to my desktop and I get the same error. I moved it back into my x86 program files and voila it works.

Read full topic

item.title: No-Ip DUC problem
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

Username and password are incorrect. What else can we say?

You also don’t HAVE to use no-ip. I don’t understand why people still do, there’s no benefit to it unless your IP is changing every week. It doesn’t hide your IP if that’s what the concern was.
